game.struct

Class Waypoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • game.struct.Waypoint
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExitPoint

    public class Waypoint
extends java.lang.Object
    Waypoint class defines flight path nodes

    Used to store target co-ordinates.

      • createWaypoint

        public Waypoint createWaypoint(double x,
                      double y)
        Creates a new hidden Waypoint

        The new Waypoint will be hidden, and inserted before the current Waypoint

        Note: this is preferred to setPrev(Waypoint) as it will maintain the state of the list

        Parameters:
        x - the point's horizontal position
        y - the point's vertical position
        Returns:
        the new Waypoint

      • createWaypoint

        public Waypoint createWaypoint(double x,
                      double y,
                      boolean visible)
        Creates a new Waypoint

        This is an alternative to createWaypoint(double, double), allowing the visibility of the new Waypoint to be set

        Note: this is preferred to setPrev(Waypoint) as it will maintain the state of the list

        Parameters:
        x - the point's horizontal position
        y - the point's vertical position
        visible - true if the point should be shown, false if the point should be hidden
        Returns:
        the new waypoint

      • deleteWaypoint

        public void deleteWaypoint()
        Removes a Waypoint

        Causes the Waypoint to be removed from the list

        Note: this will not actually delete references to the Waypoint (i.e. the Waypoint will still exist) - it will only be removed from the list of Waypoints.
